  stimulus_text = 'The author uses a series of questions to help readers understand the central point of the passage. One of the first questions is: "Does it make sense to say that the surface of the moon may not accurately reflect early impact events?" The author also asks: "How would you characterize the conclusion presented in text 1?" Finally, the author poses the following: "Would you say that it’s possible for the moon’s surface to make a decision of any kind?" What is the most likely reason why the author uses a series of questions to help readers understand the central point of the passage?',
